transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello, um, I spoke with an agent about three or four weeks ago.

Speaker 1: He gave me his extension number, 0040, and they said that wasn't an accurate extension.

Speaker 2: I don't know his name, but...

Speaker 1: Oh, you want me to transfer you?

Speaker 2: Do you know who I'm talking about?

Speaker 1: Uh, I mean, yeah, I see that you spoke to one of them. I can help you, too.

Speaker 2: Whatever works better for you.

Speaker 1: Well, I had ordered some pills that made me really dizzy.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And he sent me some that he said might be better, but they weren't.

Speaker 2: Was it you I talked to?

Speaker 1: Anyway, I said, anyway, um, I just wanted to say that I don't need any more pills

Speaker 2: since you take my name, unsubscribe me, or whatever.

Speaker 1: I'm not going to try anymore.

Speaker 2: Okay, and that's your first time taking Viagra, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: And then did you take Cialis in the past? Was Cialis a better fit for you?

Speaker 1: He sent me something different, and it wasn't any better.

Speaker 2: No, I see what he's saying, but the two calls is usually either Viagra will help you or Cialis,

Speaker 1: because they work more differently, so that's why I'm trying to evaluate

Speaker 2: what would be a better fit to help you, basically,

Speaker 1: because apparently the Viagra is not for you,

Speaker 2: because you say that even the replacement didn't work,

Speaker 1: so I'm trying to kind of evaluate what would be a better help, you know?

Speaker 2: And I don't know if you had Cialis in the past.

Speaker 1: Do you have the same problem with Cialis?

Speaker 2: Cialis, I'm just trying to understand a little bit more.

Speaker 1: Well, I tried two different ones. I don't know what they were,

Speaker 2: but I tried two different ones, and they both made me really dizzy.

Speaker 1: And I'm 80 years old, so maybe I'm just too old to take that stuff.

Speaker 2: Okay, I see. I see.

Speaker 1: I mean, you know, I wouldn't say to give up on it, maybe here and there,

Speaker 2: but, you know, your account was paused,

Speaker 1: so you can reorder as needed in the future.

Speaker 2: I think they're paused for half a year.

Speaker 1: You don't want to keep it paused just in case you need something?

Speaker 2: No. No, I'm just not going to try it anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. I'm going to cancel everything. It's okay.

Speaker 2: Just be aware of possible price change.

Speaker 1: If anything changes, try to reorder. Okay?

Speaker 2: But I'm canceling.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. Don't send me anymore.

Speaker 2: Okay. I got you, Mr. Turner.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right. You're welcome. Bye-bye.
